'''Katagatatsu Shrine''' (方県津神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Gifu City|ja|岐阜市}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県}}.
It is considered one of the {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha}} listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho}} for {{ill|Katagata District|ja|方県郡}}, {{ill|Mino Province|ja|美濃国}}. However, there are other shrines identified as possible candidates, including {{ill|Tsu Shrine|ja|津神社}} and {{ill|Agata Shrine (Gifu)|ja|縣神社_(岐阜市)|lt=Agata Shrine}}. The main shrine and worship hall are built on a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun}} (ancient Kofun).
== Enshrined Deities == * Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto
**The wife of {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi-no-Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命}}, a prince of {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王}}. She is also the mother of {{ill|Hibasu-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|日葉酢媛命|1=Hibasu-hime}}, who became the empress of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇}}.
** Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto’s father-in-law is {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王}} (enshrined at {{ill|Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|ja|伊波乃西神社|1=Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine}}). Her grandson, {{ill|Itsuninomikoto|ja|五十瓊敷入彦命}}, is enshrined at {{ill|Inaba Shrine|ja|伊奈波神社}}. The consort of Itsuninomikoto is {{ill|Nunoshihime-no-Mikoto|ja|渟熨斗姫命}}, enshrined at {{ill|Kogane Shrine|ja|金神社 (岐阜市)}}. Their son is {{ill|Ichihayao-no-Mikoto|ja|市隼雄命}}, who is the deity of {{ill|Kashimori Shrine|ja|橿森神社}}. These familial connections signify a deep relationship with the Mino Province region.
