'''Katagatatsu Shrine''' (方県津神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Gifu City|ja|岐阜市|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
It is considered one of the {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} for {{ill|Katagata District|ja|方県郡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mino Province|ja|美濃国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. However, there are other shrines identified as possible candidates, including {{ill|Tsu Shrine|ja|津神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Agata Shrine (Gifu)|ja|縣神社_(岐阜市)|lt=Agata Shrine|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. The main shrine and worship hall are built on a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (ancient Kofun).
== Enshrined Deities == * Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto
**The wife of {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi-no-Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a prince of {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. She is also the mother of {{ill|Hibasu-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|日葉酢媛命|1=Hibasu-hime|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, who became the empress of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
** Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto’s father-in-law is {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (enshrined at {{ill|Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|ja|伊波乃西神社|1=Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}). Her grandson, {{ill|Itsuninomikoto|ja|五十瓊敷入彦命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, is enshrined at {{ill|Inaba Shrine|ja|伊奈波神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. The consort of Itsuninomikoto is {{ill|Nunoshihime-no-Mikoto|ja|渟熨斗姫命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, enshrined at {{ill|Kogane Shrine|ja|金神社 (岐阜市)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Their son is {{ill|Ichihayao-no-Mikoto|ja|市隼雄命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, who is the deity of {{ill|Kashimori Shrine|ja|橿森神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. These familial connections signify a deep relationship with the Mino Province region.
== location == * 3-13-1 Yashiro, Gifu City, Gifu Prefecture
== Transportation == * Take the {{ill|Gifu Bus|ja|岐阜乗合自動車|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} Sanda-dō Line to the "Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae" bus stop. ** Board from the JR Gifu Station Bus Terminal (north exit, platform 10) or Meitetsu Gifu Bus Terminal (platform 5) heading for "K50 Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae."
