** Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto’s father-in-law is {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (enshrined at {{ill|Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|ja|伊波乃西神社|1=Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}). Her grandson, {{ill|Prince Inishikiirihiko|ja|五十瓊敷入彦命|1=Prince Inishikiirihiko|2=ja|3=五十瓊敷入彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, is enshrined at {{ill|Inaba Shrine|ja|伊奈波神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The consort of Prince Inishikiirihiko is {{ill|Nunoshihime-no-Mikoto|ja|渟熨斗姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, enshrined at {{ill|Kogane Shrine|ja|金神社 (岐阜市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Their son is {{ill|Ichihayao-no-Mikoto|ja|市隼雄命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, who is the deity of {{ill|Kashimori Shrine|ja|橿森神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. These familial connections signify a deep relationship with the Mino Province region.
== location == * 3-13-1 Yashiro, Gifu City, Gifu Prefecture
== Transportation == * Take the {{ill|Gifu Bus|ja|岐阜乗合自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Sanda-dō Line to the "Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae" bus stop. ** Board from the JR Gifu Station Bus Terminal (north exit, platform 10) or Meitetsu Gifu Bus Terminal (platform 5) heading for "K50 Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae."
