It is considered one of the {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} for {{ill|Katagata District|ja|方県郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katagata District|qq=}}, {{ill|Mino Province|ja|美濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mino Province|qq=}}. However, there are other shrines identified as possible candidates, including {{ill|Tsu Shrine|ja|津神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsu Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Agata Shrine (Gifu)|ja|縣神社_(岐阜市)|lt=Agata Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Agata Shrine (Gifu)|qq=}}. The main shrine and worship hall are built on a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun|qq=}} (ancient Kofun).
== Enshrined Deities == * Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto
**The wife of {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi-no-Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanba-no-Michinushi-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, a prince of {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|qq=}}. She is also the mother of {{ill|Hibasu-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|日葉酢媛命|1=Hibasu-hime|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hibasu-hime-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Hibasu-hime|qq=}}, who became the empress of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Suinin|qq=}}.
** Niukawakami Masurowake-no-Mikoto’s father-in-law is {{ill|Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu-no-Mikoto|qq=}} (enshrined at {{ill|Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|ja|伊波乃西神社|1=Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwa-no-Nishi Shrine|qq=}}). Her grandson, {{ill|Prince Inishikiirihiko|ja|五十瓊敷入彦命|1=Prince Inishikiirihiko|2=ja|3=五十瓊敷入彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Inishikiirihiko|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Inishikiirihiko|qq=}}, is enshrined at {{ill|Inaba Shrine|ja|伊奈波神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inaba Shrine|qq=}}. The consort of Prince Inishikiirihiko is {{ill|Nunoshihime-no-Mikoto|ja|渟熨斗姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nunoshihime-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, enshrined at {{ill|Kogane Shrine|ja|金神社 (岐阜市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kogane Shrine|qq=}}. Their son is {{ill|Ichihayao-no-Mikoto|ja|市隼雄命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichihayao-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, who is the deity of {{ill|Kashimori Shrine|ja|橿森神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashimori Shrine|qq=}}. These familial connections signify a deep relationship with the Mino Province region.
== location == * 3-13-1 Yashiro, Gifu City, Gifu Prefecture
== Transportation == * Take the {{ill|Gifu Bus|ja|岐阜乗合自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gifu Bus|qq=}} Sanda-dō Line to the "Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae" bus stop. ** Board from the JR Gifu Station Bus Terminal (north exit, platform 10) or Meitetsu Gifu Bus Terminal (platform 5) heading for "K50 Nagara Yashiro Kōen-mae."
